ce:section.ce:para:
In this work, therefore, a fluorescent NFM prepared through electrospinning was explored for both fluorescent and visual detection of cyanide. To eliminate the potential interferences from analyte-independent factors, blue-emitting carbon dots (CDs) (Lim et al., 2015; Zuo et al., 2017; Zuo et al., 2018) and red-emitting AuNCs (Xu and Shang, 2018) were explored as a ratiometric fluorescent couple, which were co-doped into the membrane during electrospinning (Scheme 1
                     ). To signal the presence of cyanide, the well-known Elsener reaction (4Au + 8CN− + 2H2O + O2 → 4Au(CN)2
                     − + 4OH−) was harvested (Liu et al., 2010; Shang et al., 2009), resulting in fluorescence quenching of AuNCs. Meanwhile, the fluorescence of CDs was not changed, thus yielding ratiometric response. Besides, such ratiometric fluorescent response can be easily observed via naked eye upon excitation with a handheld UV lamp (365 nm), leading to visual fluorescent detection (445 nm and 650 nm) of cyanide.
